body:
The dereference operator `operator*()` does not check if this optional contains a value, which may be more efficient than `value()` (https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/utility/optional/value). As `has_value()` is already checked, can also do (maybe not worth it but as a note):

```diff
         if (max_data.has_value()) {
-            if (data.size() >= max_data.value()) {
+            const size_t bytes{data.size()};
+            if (bytes >= *max_data) {
                 throw std::runtime_error(
-                    strprintf("Received too many bytes without a terminator (%u)", data.size()));
+                    strprintf("Received too many bytes without a terminator (%u)", bytes));
             }
-            peek_bytes = std::min(sizeof(buf), max_data.value() - data.size());
+            peek_bytes = std::min(sizeof(buf), *max_data - bytes);
         }
 ```

